safeFLY queries the following third-party services at runtime to display drone
geozones and weather. It does not bundle or redistribute their data. These
services are not affiliated with this project and retain all rights to their
respective data, which remains subject to each provider's own terms of use.

Drone geozone data:
  - Germany — Digitale Plattform Unbemannte Luftfahrt (DIPUL) and DFS Deutsche
    Flugsicherung GmbH (data: DFS, BKG)
  - France — Direction générale de l'Aviation civile (DGAC) via Géoportail
    (data: DGAC, IGN)
  - Switzerland — Federal Office of Civil Aviation (FOCA / BAZL) (data: FOCA,
    swisstopo)
  - Austria — Austro Control GmbH (Dronespace)
  - Czech Republic — Řízení letového provozu ČR (ŘLP ČR / ANS CR), DroneMap
  - Netherlands — Rijksoverheid, LVNL and the Ministry of Infrastructure and
    Water Management (IenW)
  - Luxembourg — Direction de l'Aviation Civile (DAC)
  - Nature reserves (Austria, Luxembourg, Netherlands) — European Environment
    Agency (EEA), Natura 2000 network

Weather data:
  - DFS Deutsche Flugsicherung GmbH — aeronautical weather (UTM weather
    service, ICON-D2 model)
  - Open-Meteo (https://open-meteo.com) — general weather forecast
